shared_text:
Plano 88
August 30 at 2:00 PM ·

Don’t forget about District 88 Meal Mondays! Pick up 5 day or 3 day meal packs, depending on your student’s school schedule. Stop by any school every Monday between 8:30-9:30 AM or 11:30-12:30 PM. Remember, school lunch status applies, so free students get 10 FREE meals, reduced cost $0.70 per pack. Full pay students will be charged full prices. Don’t miss this great opportunity to help subsidize your food budget!

¡No se olvide de los lunes de comidas del Distrito 88! Recoja paquetes de comida de 5 o 3 días, según el horario escolar de su estudiante. Pasa por cualquier escuela todos los lunes entre las 8: 30-9: 30 AM o 11: 30-12: 30 PM. Recuerde, se aplica el estado de almuerzo escolar, por lo que los estudiantes gratis obtienen 10 comidas GRATIS, costo reducido $ 0.70 por paquete. A los estudiantes de pago completo se les cobrará el precio completo. ¡No pierda esta gran oportunidad de ayudar a subsidiar su presupuesto de alimentos!

post_text: District 88 Parents, please click on this link: https://www.smore.com/naqt8 to access some very important information. We hope this will answer all of your questions as we virtually begin school for all students on Monday. Please call your school with any questions. IMPORTANT CHROME BOOK REMINDER:

Pick up Date & Times:

Wednesday, August 18 all day until 6PM
Thursday, August 19 (tomorrow) 8am -4pm

Please Note: Students can NOT use their own device at school and Remote students will need access to all teacher programs. EVERYONE will need a chrome book by this Monday, 8/24

-------------------------------------------------

RECORDATORIO IMPORTANTE DEL CHROMEBOOK:

Fecha y hora de recogida:

Miércoles 18 de agosto (hoy) todo el día hasta las 6 p.m.
Jueves, 19 de agosto (mañana) 8am -4pm

Tenga en cuenta: Los estudiantes NO pueden usar su propio dispositivo en la escuela y los estudiantes remotos necesitarán acceso a todos los programas de maestros. TODOS necesitarán un chrome book antes de este lunes 24 de agosto

Attention Centennial Elementary Students and Families.
We are working to share a 'VIRTUAL Walk-Through' of the building for students in place of the traditional Open House/Supply Drop Off event. This will be the safest way to share our facility outside of our planned, in-person structure.
As you will hear me say multiple times this year; Thank you for being flexible as we work to create the safest and most supportive teaching and learning experience for our community.

Come join us on Friday, August 21st!

Time: 6PM-8PM

Location: P.H. Miller Elementary School

Food pantry ministry will be held monthly every THIRD FRIDAY

Today, January 16, 2020, Plano High School went into Soft Lockdown, in cooperation with the Plano Police Department and Kendall County Sheriff in a K-9 search. During the time, that the soft lock down took place, it was allowed for classes to proceed as normal only restricting students from entering the hallway for approximately 30 minutes.
As always please let us know if you have any questions or concerns.
Plano Administrative Team

Hoy, 16 de enero de 2020, la Escuela Secundaria de Plano entró en Soft Lockdown, en cooperación con el Departamento de Policía de Plano y el Sheriff del Condado de Kendall en una búsqueda con el operativo de perros K-9. Durante el tiempo en que se realizó el cierre suave, se permitió que las clases se llevarán a cabo de manera normal solo restringiendo a los estudiantes el ingreso al pasillo durante aproximadamente 30 minutos.
Como siempre, háganos saber si tiene alguna pregunta o inquietud.
Equipo administrativo de Plano

Good morning Parents & Guardians. This message is to inform you Plano High School experienced a smoke detector activation due to a Science Lab experiment. This smoke detector activation set off the Fire Alarm system which prompted a swift and complete evacuation of all staff and students. After receiving an “all clear” by the Plano Fire Department, all students and staff returned to the building to continue with all daily learning activities.

Buenos días padres y tutores. Este mensaje es para informarle que, la Escuela Secundaria Plano experimentó una activación del detector de humo debido a un experimento del Laboratorio de Ciencias. Esta activación del detector de humo activó el sistema de alarma contra incendios que provocó una evacuación rápida y completa de todo el personal y los estudiantes. Después de recibir "tlux verde" por el Departamento de Bomberos de Plano, todos los estudiantes y el personal regresaron al edificio para continuar con todas las actividades de aprendizaje diarias.

post_text:
Auditions for Into the Woods

PHS' music and theatre departments will proudly present Into the Woods this spring at PHS. Any student at Plano High School is welcome to audition for the cast - no experience necessary! Auditions will be Monday, January 13 and Tuesday, January 14th from 3-5pm in the PHS auditorium. Students only need to attend one day of auditions. Material for auditions is available in the music room at this time. Callbacks, if needed, will be on Wednesday, January 15th.

To prepare for auditions, Ms. Webb and Mr. Shutack will be offering clinics on Tuesday, January 7th and Wednesday, January 8th from 3-5 in the PHS auditorium with assistance for both acting and singing. It is not required for auditioning students to attend these clinics, but it is highly encouraged.

text:
Auditions for Into the Woods

PHS' music and theatre departments will proudly present Into the Woods this spring at PHS. Any student at Plano High School is welcome to audition for the cast - no experience necessary! Auditions will be Monday, January 13 and Tuesday, January 14th from 3-5pm in the PHS auditorium. Students only need to attend one day of auditions. Material for auditions is available in the music room at this time. Callbacks, if needed, will be on Wednesday, January 15th.

To prepare for auditions, Ms. Webb and Mr. Shutack will be offering clinics on Tuesday, January 7th and Wednesday, January 8th from 3-5 in the PHS auditorium with assistance for both acting and singing. It is not required for auditioning students to attend these clinics, but it is highly encouraged.

Please email swebb@plano88.org or mshutack@plano88.org with any questions!

post_text:
The mascots for Plano Schools were happy to take part in the Rockin' Christmas parade and other festivities last weekend.

- P.H. the Panther from P.H. Miller School

- Cheetah from Centennial School

- Josie the Jaguar from Emily G. Johns School

- Ted the Tiger from Plano Middle School.

Superintendent Tony Baker, P.H. Miller Principal Laurel Mateyka and the mascots walked the parade route and joined students and their families as they welcomed in the holiday season. Santa and Mrs. Claus rode in on a Harley Davidson motorcycle and children met them at the Plano Library for pictures and refreshments. Band students from Emily G. Johns School, directed by Mr. Kevin McCammon, entertained the crowd at the historic Plano Depot.

Thank you to everyone who donated non-perishable food items, money and/or their time to make the Rockin' Christmas Program a success again this year. Happy Holidays to all Plano families!

Student/Staff for November

Plano High School “Student of the Month” for the month of November were Payton Heiden, Karla Valle, Ronald Johnson, Myia DeBolt, Eliyas Peray, Sarai Dominguez, Jorge Rizo, and Josh Benite. Students are nominated for Pride behavior, Personal Responsibility, Respect, Involved Academically, Demonstrates safe behavior, and Excellence in what they do.

Staff members for “Staff Member of the Month” for November were Mr. Ponx, Mr. Woodhouse, Mr. Love, Mrs. Minard, Ms. Gomez, Mr. Kantorski, Mrs. Adelmann, Mrs. Wells, and Ms. Franks.Staff members are nominated by going above and beyond what is expected. Staff and student members for the month process is coordinated by Courtney Voise, school counselor at Plano High School. This process is part of the Positive Behavior Intervention and Supports (PBIS) in place at Plano High School.

Yesterday, Jackie Bruns, Y Fitness Instructor & Personal Trainer, visited pre-K classes at PH Miller School to talk to them about the importance of staying active. Jackie led a kid-friendly exercise class where kids learned to move like animals. #FVFYMCA #YWeStandOut

"All 3 of my kids attended PH Millers and 2 of my 3 went through the preschool program. I’m happy to give back to PH Miller because of how much they gave to my children and in appreciation of how much the staff and administration care about the kids. Also, with childhood obesity being an epidemic, any opportunity I have to promote exercise and wellness to the next generation, I jump at the chance!" -Jackie Bruns

post_text:
Waubonsee Community College is offering a new event on November 21, 2019 titled Countdown to College.
The event is designed for future Waubonsee students and parents and offers an opportunity to complete the Waubonsee New Student Information Form, the FAFSA, learn about scholarships and the application process, see a presentation on Choosing a Career and much more!

ESPAÑOL
Waubonsee Community College ofrecerá un nuevo evento el 21 de noviembre de 2019 titulado Countdown to College.
El evento está diseñado para futuros estudiantes y padres de Waubonsee y ofrece la oportunidad de completar el Formulario de información para nuevos estudiantes de Waubonsee, la FAFSA, aprender sobre becas y el proceso de solicitud, ver una presentación sobre cómo elegir una carrera y mucho más.

post_text:
Treats on the Street - Tuesday, October 29 from 4-6 PM on Main Street in Plano, Reaper Center and Arts on Fire parking lots in Plano. Safe trick or treating at Plano businesses.

Kids, put on your Halloween costumes and visit Plano area businesses for some fun treats. This years event has expanded from downtown Plano to Reaper Center and all the way to the Arts on Fire parking lot. Local businesses will have some fun games in the parking lot of Arts on Fire.
